<% content_for :description, "How Remindly collects, uses, and protects the information you and the people you care for share with it." %>

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p class="lead">
  Remindly holds sensitive information — medication routines, appointments, and
  who is caring for whom. This page explains, in plain language, what we collect,
  why, and the choices you have.
</p>

<p><em>Last updated: July 24, 2026.</em></p>

<h2>Who we are</h2>
<p>
  Remindly is operated by Anakhsoft ("we", "us"). If you have any question about
  your information, write to
  <a href="mailto:hello@remindly.care">hello@remindly.care</a> and a real person
  will answer.
</p>

<h2>What we collect</h2>
<p>We only collect what the service needs to work:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Your account.</strong> Your email address, and optionally a name,
    nickname, and time zone, along with your role (whether you receive reminders,
    care for someone who does, or both) and your notification preferences.
    Remindly has no passwords — you sign in through a one-time link we email you.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Reminders and care information.</strong> The reminders you create —
    their titles and notes (which may name a medication or an appointment), when
    they recur, and whether each one was marked done, snoozed, or missed, with the
    time it happened — plus any periods you mark as unavailable. This is the heart
    of what Remindly does, and some of it is health-related.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Caregiver relationships.</strong> The links between a senior and their
    caregivers, invitations and pairing codes used to set them up, caregivers'
    stated availability, and any tasks or comments used to coordinate care.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>A connected calendar (only if you add one).</strong> A caregiver can
    connect an external scheduling account (Acuity Scheduling) so appointments
    appear as tasks. If you do, we store the access credentials needed to sync and
    the appointment details we bring in. You can disconnect it at any time.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Basic usage analytics.</strong> For signed-in activity we record
    ordinary technical details — IP address, browser and device type, the page
    referring you, and any campaign tags in the link you followed — to understand
    how the service is used and to diagnose problems. We do <strong>not</strong>
    collect this on the public marketing pages, we do not look up your physical
    location, and we do not use third-party advertising or tracking services.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>How we use it</h2>
<ul>
  <li>To speak and display reminders to the person they are for, at the right time.</li>
  <li>To tell caregivers, in the app and by email, when a reminder is completed or missed — for the categories each caregiver has chosen.</li>
  <li>To sign you in, using the one-time link we email you.</li>
  <li>To help caregivers coordinate: tasks, availability, and coverage.</li>
  <li>To keep the service running, secure, and working correctly.</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not sell your information, and we do not use it for advertising.</p>

<h2>Email</h2>
<p>
  We send email through <a href="https://postmarkapp.com">Postmark</a>, our email
  provider, for sign-in links and for the caregiver notifications described above.
  Your email address is shared with Postmark only to deliver those messages.
</p>

<h2>Who else can see it</h2>
<p>
  Your care information is visible to you and to the caregivers linked to the
  senior it belongs to. Beyond that, we share information only with the service
  providers that run Remindly on our behalf:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>DigitalOcean</strong> — hosts the servers where your data is stored.</li>
  <li><strong>Postmark</strong> — delivers our email.</li>
  <li><strong>Acuity Scheduling</strong> — only if a caregiver connects it, to sync appointments.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  We may also disclose information if the law requires it, or to protect the
  safety of a person using Remindly.
</p>

<h2>Cookies</h2>
<p>
  When you are signed in, we use a cookie to keep you signed in, and cookies to
  measure the usage described above. Visitors who are not signed in are not given
  an analytics cookie on our public pages.
</p>

<h2>How long we keep it</h2>
<p>
  Usage analytics are automatically deleted after 90 days. Your account and care
  information is kept for as long as your account is active so the service can
  work. When you ask us to delete your data, we will.
</p>

<h2>Your choices</h2>
<ul>
  <li>You can change your notification preferences, name, and time zone from your profile at any time.</li>
  <li>A caregiver can disconnect a linked calendar at any time.</li>
  <li>You can ask us to show you, correct, or delete the information we hold about you — email <a href="mailto:hello@remindly.care">hello@remindly.care</a> and we will take care of it.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Security</h2>
<p>
  Remindly has no passwords to steal — you sign in with a one-time link — and the
  site is served over encrypted (HTTPS) connections. No service can promise
  perfect security, but we work to protect your information and to limit who can
  reach it.
</p>

<h2>Where your data is processed</h2>
<p>
  Remindly runs on servers provided by DigitalOcean. Depending on where you are,
  your information may be processed in a country other than your own.
</p>

<h2>Children</h2>
<p>
  Remindly is made for adults — seniors and the people who care for them — and is
  not directed at children.
</p>

<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
<p>
  If we change how we handle your information, we will update this page and its
  "last updated" date. Significant changes will be communicated to the people
  affected.
</p>

<div class="note">
  <p>
    Questions about your privacy? Email
    <a href="mailto:hello@remindly.care">hello@remindly.care</a>.
  </p>
</div>
